Sorry for not getting back to you sooner, would love to get a copy of the return objects to replicate this myself. Unfortunately I don't have an Office 365 subscription to test out the code. If you are ok with sharing the log output that would be great;

To enable logging, create a file called `log.json` with the following contents

```
{
    "version": 1,
    "disable_existing_loggers": false,
    "formatters": {
        "simple": {
            "format": "%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s"
        }
    },

    "handlers": {
        "file": {
            "class": "logging.FileHandler",
            "level": "DEBUG",
            "formatter": "simple",
            "filename": "pypsrp.log",
            "mode": "w",
            "encoding": "utf-8"
        }
    },

    "loggers": {
        "pypsrp.messages": {
            "level": "DEBUG",
            "handlers": ["file"],
            "propagate": "no"
        }
    }
}
```

Run the Python script with the `PYPSRP_LOG_CFG=log.json` environment variable and a file called `pypsrp.log` will be created. Please make sure you are comfortable sharing the contents of the log online as this will contain all the PSRP messages sent to and from the client. If you aren't comfortable with this you can change/remove the values as I'm mostly interested in the structure/types and references in the message itself.

