This happens because the lenses library doesn't know that a `frozenset` can be constructed from an iterable. You can work around it by adding the following code somewhere in your code base:

``` python
import lenses.hooks
@lenses.hooks.from_iter.register(frozenset)
def _frozenset_from_iter(self, iterable):
    return frozenset(iterable)
```

This hook will be included by default in the next release.

