@Soonhwan-Kwon @piiswrong 
Glad to hear the tutorial was helpful for your project but the question really is whether it belong in the repo. We're trying to improve the quality of examples and would like to move to a world where the examples can be automatically validated for each release. If preprocessing the data using the external ASR tool Kaldi takes days then I propose that the tutorial should not be included in the repo.

if someone with expertise in ASR were to prepare some sample data that could be used with the reference network architecture then perhaps a new example tutorial could be created in the future, but for now let's remove it so it doesn't cause confusion on the web site for people who are new to MXNet.

