@daspecster @tseaver I'll update the PR to use `datetime.datime` instances instead of `str`. I have a question though. Where should we convert the `datetime.datime` to RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format ([docs](https://cloud.google.com/logging/docs/api/reference/rest/v2/LogEntry))? It could be done in the [write_entry](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/blob/115748814bf6a59d99c13e070dfdcfbdec5e865d/logging/google/cloud/logging/_http.py#L131) method. This would look like:

```python
def write_entries(self, entries, logger_name=None, resource=None, labels=None):
        data = {'entries': [_prepare_entry(entry) for entry in entries]}
    
        if logger_name is not None:
            data['logName'] = logger_name
    
        if resource is not None:
            data['resource'] = resource
    
        if labels is not None:
            data['labels'] = labels
    
        self._connection.api_request(method='POST', path='/entries:write',
                                     data=data)
```
With `_prepare_entry` a function that would rely on the [_datetime_to_rfc3339](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/blob/aea151b83893656e43d563935de8ce93a46f310a/core/google/cloud/_helpers.py#L311) function to convert timestamp into RFC3339.

Would you have a more elegant solution ?

