@ahayschi, I'm able to reproduce this error. Here's what is happening:

You are running a fairly up to date version of Parsl from github. On EC2 remote side, you have got parsl v0.5.0 installed from PyPI. The recently added wrapper code imports a module that is not available on the remote side which uses v0.5.0. This code path is hit only when the app code raises an error. So the problem simply boils down a version mismatch.

We'll put out a point release soon (targetting next week) which will fix this issue.
